commitResults.messageBody:
Initial skeletal version of Duke which greets the user, echos
commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye.

Customise greeting at the start of the program. Modularise program
reponse into separate methods depending on user input, to increase
maintainability and readability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the ability to store and display user input
commitResults.messageBody:
Store text entered by the user in a list, and display the list
when the user types list.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor tasks into a Task class
commitResults.messageBody:
Abstract tasks into a separate class. Modify Duke to handle a list
of tasks instead of strings containing task descriptions.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the ability to mark tasks as done
commitResults.messageBody:
Mark a task as done when the user types done, followed by the
number indicating the position of the task in the list of tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement multiple task types through inheritance
commitResults.messageBody:
Convert Task to an abstract class. Implement Todo, Deadline, and
Event classes that inherit from the Task class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for 3 types of tasks: Todo, Deadline, and Event
commitResults.messageBody:
Create the appropriate types of tasks depending on user input, and
add them to the list of tasks.
Remove newline character at the end of each response message.

Add a bash script that employs redirection to test Duke using
input from `input.txt`, and compare the output with the expected
output in `EXPECTED.TXT`.

Add exceptions for empty tasks, missing information, and
unrecognised commands.

Edit the javac command to look for classes in `../src/main/java`
instead of compiling all the java files in that directory.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement exceptions for invalid task selection
commitResults.messageBody:
Add InvalidTaskException for general exceptions in selecting a
task, and InvalidTaskNumberException for exceptions due to task
numbers not corresponding to any task in the list.

Vary the tone of some error messages to give Duke more of its own
personality.

Add custom exception to be thrown when commands that expect a
task number do not receive any additional arguments.
Modify Duke to handle incorrect user input.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for deleting tasks from the list
Store deadline dates as LocalDate objects
commitResults.messageBody:
Accept deadlines in yyyy-mm-dd format, and display them in
d MMM yyyy format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to save tasks automatically
commitResults.messageBody:
Save the task list in `duke/data/duke.txt` and load the tasks from
the file when Duke starts, if it exists.

Create a package `duke` containing all the java files used for the
Duke program. Modify the test script to compile and run Duke using
the correct file paths.
